revision.text:
{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}} {{Use British English|date=May 2015}} '''Sir Einar Athelstan Gordon Caroe''' [[Commander of the British Empire|CBE]] (6 October 1903 – 18 April 1988) was a grain merchant and broker with the firm of W.S. Williamson and Co., Liverpool. He was born in [[Blundellsands]], [[Lancashire]], and died in [[Scorton, Lancashire]].<ref>''[http://www.abps.org.uk/Awards/Roll_of_Distinguished_Philatelists/RDP_Background_20111231_LR.pdf Background notes on The Roll of Distinguished Philatelists September 2011]'', Roll of Distinguished Philatelists Trust, London, 2011. [https://www.webcitation.org/6OlHSBOTl Archived here.]</ref>
Caroe was chairman of the [[Trustee Savings Banks Association]],<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=KJZAAAAAIBAJ&pg=2986%2C4683798 | title=Savings banks want to enter personal loan stakes | first=David | last=Jones | newspaper=The Glasgow Herald | date=24 February 1972 | page=15 | accessdate=16 July 2015 }}</ref> honorary president of the EEC Savings Bank Group and a director of the [[Norwich Union|Norwich Union Group]].{{citation needed|date=March 2015}}. He was Chairman on Minton Limited until its sale to Royal Doulton in 1968. Caroe was also consul for Denmark and Iceland in Liverpool.{{citation needed|date=March 2015}}
He was appointed a [[Knight Bachelor]] in January 1972.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=kNE9AAAAIBAJ&pg=1563%2C117816 | title=Five Scots among 34 new knights | date=3 January 1972 | newspaper=The Glasgow Herald | page=9 | accessdate=16 July 2015 }}</ref>
==Family== Caroe married twice, first to Frances Mary Lyon on 6 April 1934 (Mary was descended from Thomas Minton and Colin Minton Campbell) they two sons Charles Frederick Caroe (13 May 1935 to 1 August 2012) and Andrew Minton Campbell. Mary died from polio in 1948. Athelstan married Doreen Evelen Jane Sandland in 1952 (known as Jane). They had three children Clarissa, John and Patrick. Jane died in Lancaster, 21 April 2003.{{citation needed|date=March 2015}} John died at birth and Patrick in 2014 at the age of 49.
==Philately== In his spare time, Caroe was a noted [[philatelist]] who was added to the [[Roll of Distinguished Philatelists]] in 1972.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.abps.org.uk/Home/Who_Was_Who/index.xalter#C | title=Who Was Who in Philately | publisher=The Association of British Philatelic Societies | accessdate=16 July 2015 }}</ref> Athelstan was an able tennis player in his youth competing in mixed double at county level with his wife Mary, no doubt helped by his height (6'5").
