{{Infobox university | name = CUNY School of Labor and Urban Studies | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = | image_upright = | image_alt = | caption = | latin_name = | other_name = <!--or, other_names--> | former_name = <!--or, former_names--> | motto = | motto_lang = | mottoeng = | top_free_label = | top_free = | type = | established = {{start date|2018}} | closed = <!-- {{end date|YYYY}} --> | founder = Gregory Mantsios | parent = | affiliation = [[City University of New York]] | religious_affiliation = | academic_affiliation = | endowment = | budget = | officer_in_charge = | chairman = | chairperson = | chancellor = | president = | vice-president = | superintendent = | vice_chancellor = | provost = | rector = | principal = | dean = Gregory Mantsios | director = | head_label = | head = | academic_staff = | administrative_staff = | students = | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | city = New York City | state = NY | province = | country = USA | postcode = <!--or, postalcode or zipcode--> | coor = {{coord|40.754894|-73.981856|region:US_type:edu|display=inline,title}} | campus = Urban | language = | free_label = | free = | free_label2 = | free2 = | colors = <!--or, colours= --> | athletics = | sports = | athletics_nickname = <!--or, sports_nickname= --> | sporting_affiliations = | mascot = <!--or, mascots= --> | sports_free_label = | sports_free = | sports_free_label2 = | sports_free2 = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | logo = File:CUNY_School_of_Labor_and_Urban_Studies_Logo.png | logo_size = | logo_alt = | footnotes = }}
'''CUNY School of Labor and Urban Studies''' (also known as '''SLU''') is a public undergraduate, graduate, and professional school in [[New York City]] associated with the [[City University of New York]] system. Founded in 2018 as an outgrowth of the [[CUNY School of Professional Studies|Joseph S. Murphy Institute for Worker Education and Labor Studies]], the Murphy Institute is now one of incorporated programs at the School of Labor and Urban Studies, which provides undergraduate and graduate degrees in Labor Studies and Urban Studies, as well as certificate programs and [[workforce development]] for members of labor unions.<ref name=school_facts>{{cite web |url=http://www1.cuny.edu/sites/lus/about/school-facts/ |title=School Facts |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2018 |website=CUNY School of Labor and Urban Studies |publisher=City University of New York |access-date=July 30, 2018 |quote=}}</ref>
==History== The CUNY School of Labor and Urban Studies was established in 2018 as an outgrowth of the Joseph S. Murphy Institute for Worker Education and Labor Studies, otherwise known as The Murphy Institute. The Murphy Institute was first established in 1984 at [[Queens College, City University of New York|Queens College]] in collaboration with three New York City labor unions for the purposes of providing worker education to labor union members.<ref name=school_facts /> In 2005, the Murphy Institute was incorporated into CUNY's School of Professional Studies, expanding to provide undergraduate and graduate degrees.<ref name=dean>{{cite web |url=http://www1.cuny.edu/sites/lus/about/welcome/ |title=Welcome From the Dean |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2018 |website=CUNY School of Labor and Urban Studies |publisher=City University of New York |access-date=July 30, 2018 |quote=}}</ref>
Though New York labor unions had been petitioning for the Murphy Institute to become its own stand-alone school since 2012, when the New York State [[AFL-CIO]] passed a resolution endorsing the proposal, it was only until Governor [[Andrew Cuomo]] added $1.5 million to the state budget in 2018 that funding was available.<ref name=nypost>{{cite news |last=Campanile |first=Chris |date=March 26, 2018 |title=Cuomo’s budget includes plan to create CUNY school focused on unions |url=https://nypost.com/2018/03/26/cuomos-budget-includes-plan-to-create-cuny-school-focused-on-unions/ |work=[[New York Post]] |location=New York City |access-date=July 30, 2018 }}</ref>
==Faculty== As of 2018, CUNY School of Labor and Urban Studies employs fifteen faculty, some of whom have shared appointments with other universities in the CUNY system.<ref name=faculty>{{cite web |url=http://www1.cuny.edu/sites/lus/about/faculty/ |title=Faculty |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2018 |website=CUNY School of Labor and Urban Studies |publisher=City University of New York |access-date=July 30, 2018 |quote=}}</ref> Among the faculty include: {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * [[Mimi Abramovitz]] * [[Stanley Aronowitz]] * [[Juan Battle]] * [[Francis Fox Piven]] * [[Joshua Freeman]] * [[Ruth Milkman]] * [[John Mollenkopf]] {{div col end}}
