{{Other people|John Delaney|John Delaney (disambiguation){{!}}John Delaney}} {{Infobox person | name = John Delaney | image = | caption = | birth_date = 1969 | birth_place = [[Ireland]] | death_date = 21 May 2011 (aged 42) | death_place = [[Mount Everest]] | occupation = [[Businessman]] }}
'''John Delaney''' (1969 – 21 May 2011) was an Irish businessman and the [[CEO]] of the [[betting exchange|trading exchange]] website [[Intrade]] from 2003 until 2011, which was the first commercial online exchange to feature trading on election outcomes.
Delaney died at the age of 42 while attempting to climb [[Mount Everest]]—a lifelong ambition—and came within 50 metres of the summit. He is survived by his wife (Orla), two sons (Caspar and Alexander) and a daughter (Hope) who was born whilst Delaney was away on the expedition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/27/business/27delaney.html?ref=deathsobituaries|title=John Delaney, Founder of Intrade, Dies at 42|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=May 26, 2011|author=Julie Creswell}}</ref>
